&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6447&quot; title=&quot;Use StrictMath for more functions in SYSFUN&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-6447&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-6447&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Use StrictMath for more functions in SYSFUN&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Make LOG10, COSH, SINH and TANH use the corresponding methods in&lt;br/&gt;
java.lang.StrictMath instead of custom implementations.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13867781" author="knutanders" created="Fri, 10 Jan 2014 13:28:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We should probably have a release note for this issue, so that users of these functions are notified that the results may change after they upgrade.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13869819" author="dagw" created="Mon, 13 Jan 2014 18:44:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1; I think that&apos;s prudent.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
